node.text:
I had an amazing experience this morning speaking to students at Tri-Cities High School in East Point, GA. Thank you to Principal Ethel Lett for having me! 

I grew up like many of the students and delivered a message that I would have wanted to hear about getting good grades, being involved, and going after their goals and dreams. Just because you grow up poor, doesn’t mean you have to have poor dreams!

A big thank you to Mike Triplett and the @cignatogether team for putting this together.
